The paper discusses a networking protocol, specifically the FAST-TCP protocol, and its performance in terms of fairness and throughput. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm to improve the protocol's performance, which could fall under Information Theory (cs.IT) or Communications (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the persistent congestion problem, which could be related to Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
